==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rhinencephalon
<hw>Rhi`nen*ceph"a*lon</hw>
<pr>(r⟦imac⟧`n⟦ecr⟧n*s⟦ecr⟧f"⟦adot⟧*l⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Rhinencephala</plw>
<pr>(r⟦imac⟧`n⟦ecr⟧n*s⟦ecr⟧f"⟦adot⟧*l⟦adot⟧)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>"ri`s</grk>, <grk>"rino`s</grk>, the nose +
<grk>'egke`falos</grk> the brain.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The
division of the brain in front of the prosencephalon, consisting of the
two olfactory lobes from which the olfactory nerves arise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term is sometimes used for one of the olfactory
lobes, the plural being used for the two taken together.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhinestone</ent>⟦br⟧
